sentences: Zahera Darabid (Arabic: زهيرة درابيد ; born May 10, 1980), known by her stage name Zaho (), is an Algerian-Canadian R&B singer.
Zahera Darabid was born on May 10, 1980, in Bab Ezzouar, a suburb of the Algerian capital Algiers.
Zaho learned the guitar when she was seven years old, and very quickly learned the répertoire of Francis Cabrel within 10 years.
Zaho learned the guitar when she was seven years old, and very quickly learned the répertoire of Francis Cabrel within 10 years.
In 1999, when she emigrated to Montreal, she discovered the world of professional music with its producers and its studios.
In 2008, she released her debut album titled Dima, meaning Always in Arabic.
In 2008, Zaho represented France in the 2008 MTV EMA's and won the Best European Artist award.
